name: Crab Rangoon III
author: lavaun
summary: Crabmeat and cream cheese wontons make excellent appetizers. Leave out the water chestnuts, if desired. Serve with your favorite Asian-style dipping sauces.
ingredients: 2 (6 ounce) cans crabmeat, drained and flaked
2 tablespoons water chestnuts, drained and chopped
directions: In a large, heavy sauce pan heat oil to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
In a medium bowl, mix cream cheese, crabmeat, garlic powder, paprika and water chestnuts
Place approximately 1 teaspoon of the cream cheese mixture in the center of wonton wrappers
Moisten wrapper edges with water, fold over the mixture and pinch to seal
In small batches, fry the wontons 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden brown
